    • Uses of CaseBaseFilter in org.jLOAF.preprocessing.filter.casebasefilter

      Subclasses of CaseBaseFilter in org.jLOAF.preprocessing.filter.casebasefilter 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ActionClustering
      this class clusters the CaseBase based on the number of actions the domain used has.
      class  Clustering
      this class is used to cluster casebases, it puts similar cases in one cluster,the picks one of them to add it to the new casebase removing almost duplicated cases
      class  FullClustering 
      class  KClustering 
      class  NoFilter 
      class  Sampling
      Preprocess the CaseBase by only adding a case into the CaseBase if the prediction of the action using the current CaseBase is wrong return the new CaseBase
      class  UnderSampling
      This class undersamples the majority class by randomly removing a percentage of the majority class cases based on the value of underSamplePercent which can range from [0,1] where 1 represents equalizing the majority and minority classes, and 0 represents not removing cases.

    • Uses of CaseBaseFilter in org.jLOAF.preprocessing.filter.featureSelection

      Subclasses of CaseBaseFilter in org.jLOAF.preprocessing.filter.featureSelection 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  FeatureSelectionAlgorithm
      this class extends the caseBaseFilter class and follows the decorator design pattern as well, but it also the parent of all the classes that has to do with the weights of the features, usually this filters are used when the inputs used in the cases have a weightedMean similarity.
      class  GeneticAlgorithmWeightSelector
      This method will take a casebase that has some similarityWeights for every feature and determine the best weights for each feature.
      class  HillClimbingFeatureSelection
      this class takes the original list of weights and calculates its performance accuracy, it keeps comparing this accuracy to the accuracy of this list's neighbors.
      class  SequentialBackwardGeneration
      The Sequential Backward Generation wrapper algorithm described in R.
      class  WeightsSeperatorFilter
      this class checks the weights of the features of all the cases, when a weight of a feature is zero, it removes it from the list of the features that the cases have.(here by features we mean inputs).
